{{Quote|In fact, there are many similarities between this 'new' magazine and its predecessor. The major difference begins with the key word in the revised title: ''Collector''. This magazine will now be the definitive, official source of information on all the toys, vehicles, figurines, comics and every other collectible that has been covered by ''Star Wars'' fans for more than 20 years.|''Star Wars Galaxy Collector'' editor Bob Woods|<ref name="RR">{{CollectorCite|1|Rebel Report}}</ref>}}
'''''Star Wars Galaxy Collector''''', abbreviated as '''''SWGC''''', was a magazine published quarterly by [[Topps]] that focused on ''[[Star Wars]]'' collectibles. The successor to Topps' previous ''Star Wars'' publication, ''[[Star Wars Galaxy Magazine]]'', ''Star Wars Galaxy Collector'' ran for eight issues, from [[February]] [[1998]] to [[December]] [[1999]].

Subscriber copies of ''Star Wars Galaxy Collector'', dubbed Deluxe Collectors' Editions, came polybagged with exclusive ''Star Wars'' collectibles, such as Topps trading cards. The Deluxe Collectors' Editions were offered only to subscribers and comic stores, and were not available on newsstands. Each ''Star Wars Galaxy Collector'' issue included a special fold-out poster, self-contained within the newsstand editions or loose within the the Deluxe Collectors' Editions' exclusive polybags.

